===Noun===
'''{{PAGENAME}}'''
# French for coffee-maker.  It means a coffee jug.  Typically it will be cylindrical, and it will have a rod with a knob on the end sticking vertically out of the lid.  On the bottom end of this rod (inside the jug) is a flat horizontal filter that covers the cross-section of the jug.  When the coffee has finished brewing (and before you pour it) you push the knob all the way down to the lid, and the filter keeps the ground coffee at the bottom of the jug.  I believe this has something to do with the taste, but I only ever drink instant coffee, so I wouldn't know.  You can help Wiktionary by deleting these last two sentences.

